nt.\nI:4s\u2014John Barclay.\n2:oo\u2014Roxy Symphony Orchestra.\n3:00 \u2014Youth Conference.\n4:00 \u2014Sunday Feature.\n4:15 \u2014Musical Crusaders.\n4:45 \u2014Feature Music.\ns:oo\u2014Vespers.\n6:oo\u2014Raising Junior.\n6:00 \u2014Margaret Olsen.\n6:ls\u2014Concert.\n7:00 \u2014Harbor Lights.\n7:30 \u2014Josef Koestner\u2019s Orchestra.\n8:00 \u2014Mme. Schumann-Heink.\nB:ls\u2014Uncle Henry\u2019s Magazine.\n9:ls\u2014lslanders.\n9:30 \u2014Floyd Gibbons, Talk.\n10:00 \u2014Dean Sisters.\n10:15\u2014Pete\u2019s Storiee.\n10:30\u2014Lew White.\n11:00 \u201481umber Music.\n11:80 \u2014Reminiscence*.\n272.6\u2014WPG\u20141,110.\n6:ls\u2014Organ Concert.\n6:4s\u2014Goepel Hymns.\n7:oo\u2014Concert Orchestra.\n9:ls\u2014Musical Programs.\n10:00 \u2014The Poet.\n10:30\u2014 WABC UV2 hours).\n282.8\u2014W8AL\u20141,860.\n6:oo\u2014Romany Trail.\n6:30 \u2014Evening Reveries.\n7:00\u2014Baltimoreans.\n422.3\u2014W0R\u2014715.\n6:3o\u2014Globe Trotter.\n6:45 \u2014Choir Invisible.\n7:4s\u2014Ensemble.\n8:30 \u2014Entertainers.\n9:00 \u2014Musical.\n9:30 \u2014Symphony Orchestra.\n10:30 \u2014Playhouse.\n11:30 \u2014The Moonbeams.\n379.5\u2014WGY\u2014790,\n6:00 \u2014Same as WEAF.\n7:oo\u2014Concert.\n7:3O\u2014WEAF (4Vj hours).\nI The HUB Furniture Co. 7th D Sts. N. W. \u2014The HUB Furniture Co.\nLet's Take A Look At What The Hub I\nI\nmatched butt walnut front panels and s\u00bb 7-Ttibc Model I\napron. Equipped with the \u201cquick-vision\u201d 3 Q vm J\\|*| U I\natcuralrs. l t JK\u00ab\u00ab\u00a3 8 RCA Radiola rhilco Console m\nPay Next Year fj SI Tl 6 C ompl\u00ab. S BB'\u00b0\u00b0 Com P let\n111 I D L- f I J' \u00a33\u00a3 Come In and listen to its mellow, life- anything else near the price. See and\nf\\\\i V n lx. PI Cl I like tone, examine the excellence of hear It\u2014we 11 let you be the judge. Its\nI IIIV. Cl UOUy VJ Ia I ICI l>auiu cabinet design and finish. Latest type tone and accuracy in locating stations\n1 1.1 \u2014l.\u2014l\nHUB Radio Service rvflCl I BID No Added Cost for Hi\nP Is Supreme J Deferred B\nBuy at the HUB Seventh and D Sts. N.W. Payments on Radios\nEducator Proposes\nTwo Watts Station\nCosting Only SSO\nThis being an era for higher\npower for broadcasting, it came\nalmost a* a shock to the Federal\nRadio Commission when G. T.\nRugland, high school superin\ntendent at Appleton, Minn., ap\nplied for authority to erect a\nnew broadcasting station to op\nerate with only 2 watts of power\non the wave length of 1,310 kilo\ncycles.\nTwo small tubes of the type\nused in the average radio receiv\ning set would be employed to con\ntrol the power output of this tiny\nstation, which, according to the\napplicant, would cost only SSO to\nerect. Mr. Rugland asks permis\nsion to be on the air only five\ndaytime hours and one evening\nhour each week in order \"to give\nexpression to the talent of the\npupils of this community.\u201d\nThe lowest powered broadcast\ning station now operating in this\ncountry is WQDM, St. Albans,\nVt., using 5 watts on 1,370 kilo\ncycles, but Its owner, A. J. St.\nAntoine, has just applied to the\ncommission for an increase to\n100 watts. Commission engineers\nrecall that in the last few years\nthere have been applications for\nnew stations to use one-tenth of\n1 watt and three-fourths of 1\nwatt, both of which were,denied.\nCENTRAL AND SOUTHERN\nSTATIONS.\n428.3\u2014WLW\u2014709.\n6:3O\u2014R. F. D. Program.\n7:00 \u2014Orchestra.\n7:30 \u2014Same as WJZ.\n8:00 \u2014Variety.\n8:15 \u2014Same as WJZ.\n9:15 \u2014Jolly Time.\n9:30 \u2014Same as WJZ.\n10:00 \u2014Orchestra: WJZ.\n11:30 \u2014Orchestras.\n398.8\u2014WJRr\u2014750.\n6:30 \u2014The Welcomers.\n7:00 \u2014Shadows.\n7:15 \u2014Sweethearts.\n7:3o\u2014Garden Melody.\nB:OO\u2014 WJZ (1% hour*).\n9:16 \u2014Serenaders.\n9:30 \u2014Same as WJZ.\n10:00\u2014Lyric Poets.\n10:30\u2014Heaven and Horn*.\n11:00 \u2014Same as WJZ.\n405.2\u2014W58\u2014740.\n7:00 \u2014Sponsored Program.\n7:30 \u2014Same as WEAF.\n8:00 \u2014Same as WJZ.\nB:ls\u2014Baker Boys.\n8:30 \u2014Same as WEAF.\n10:15 \u2014Same as WJZ.\n10:30 \u2014M. E. Church.\n11:15\u2014Bright Spot.\n11:45 \u2014Same as WEAF.\n12:00\u2014 Journal Program.\n\nHome-makers i\nTUNE IN\nMenus..R eci he s.. Samples\nChi Id Care hints... Other ideas galore l\nRADIO HOUSEHOLD INSTITUTE\nStation WRC II:IS every morning\n\u201cFEMALE RUDY VALLEE\u201d\nINSPIRES ROMANCE\nVoice of Leona Dragon of WSMB\nParticularly Adapted to Sen\ntimental Songs.\nNEW ORLEANS (ip. \u2014Her singing\nshould fill any one with romance.\nThat\u2019s the way a radio fan described\nher reaction after hearing a program\nby Leona Dragon from WSMB.\nMiss Dragon has been called the \u201cfe\nmale Rudy Vallee\u201d by New Orleans\nnewspaper critics. Her voice is particu\nlarly adapted to sentimental ballads.\nShe has been a feature artist on the\nmusic salon program of WSMB for 18\nmonths. During that time she has\nbroadcast more than 100 programs\nwithout making a single \u201cmicrographic\u201d\nerror.\n\nBAN STREET NOISES\nAdvertising Loud-Speakers Arc\nForbidden in Brussels.\nBRUSSELS UP. Burgomasters of the\nlocalities situated on the outskirts of\nthe Belgian capital decided to recom\nmend the general application of a Brus\nsels police regulation against street\nnoises.\nOne article provides that no radio\nloud speaker may be operated with an\nadvertising purpose in streets and open\nplaces.\nSeek Radio for Mecca.\nMECCA, Arabia (ip. \u2014Taking note of\nother groups\u2019 utilization of the radio to\nspread their doctrines, Ibn Saud, ruler\nof the Wahabis and keeper of the\nIslamic holy places, Mecca and Medina,\nis negotiating with British wireless\nmanufacturers preparatory to Installing\na transmitter here.\nRadio Service\nj Phone\nAdam* 3803\na Sc. Col. Rd.\nUo Service tr Town f,\nlywvwHC\u00dfgiMTweciiymggJ\n/%,y>\nRADIO JAZZ IN U. S.\nLEADING EUROPE\nRatio of 83.9 to 7 Per Cent Fonnd\n.t 1 r\nf I>y Government Expert*.\nAdvertising Leads.\nJazz music is more prominent on the\nradio programs of this country than in\nEurope.\nResearch by Government experts dis\nclosed that European radio programs\nt carry only 7 per cent dance and Jazz\ni music as compared with 33.9 per cent\ni for the United States.\nMusic was found to occupy 58.51 ;.r\ncent of European programs and 52.96\nper cent of United States programs.\nEurope devoted 18.09 per cent of its\nradio time to formal education, includ\ning 4 per cent to le tures. While the\nUnited States gave only 1.08 per cent\n1 of its time to formal education, this\ncountry used 19.12 per cent to Informal\neducation which had no counterpart in\nEurope.\nThe United States gave 8.64 per cent\nof Its programs to advertising, as\nagainst no time for this in Europe.\nNew Woman Announcer Named.\n\u201cRadio Torino\u201d at Turin, Italy, has\nselected Signora Maria Corsius as Its\nnew woman radio announcer. She\nqualified in a field of 180 candidates,\nnot only for her pleasing voice, but for\nher ability to read market reports in a\nclever and original manner. They have\na predilection for woman announcers\nin Italy.\n\nl\n:T<\u00a3> Radio:\nx V\\ SERVice\nXf* <SErw<w J\nBABY j\nl GRAND\n49 *5 I\nX DOWN\nI LESS TUBE!\nX Free Delivery\u2014Free Imettilatien X\nO. K. Service\nOKAY RADIO COMPANY\n41711th St. N.W. 1760 Fa. Ays. N.W.\n1,752,000 RECEIVERS\nIN NEW YORK STATE\nNevada, With Only One Station,\nHas But 83,000 Kadio Seta,\nSurvey Bevealg.\nThe number of listeners in various\nsections of the country corresponds al\nmost invariably wit', the number of\nbroadcasting: stations in those areas.\nA survey by engineers of the Federal\nRadio Commissioners shows that\u2014\nNew York state, with Its heavy con\ncentration of stations In the metro\npolitan district, has an estimated 1,752,-\n000 receivers.\nNevada, with only one station, has\n[monarch]\nS Ts,\u2018 RADIO SHOP 1\nI I FEATURING I\nR.C.A. Radiola\nThe newest, smartest\nlUrSli lllf rfW model full size i\njo I|| W m /fll chassis, not a miniature f\nIjl namic speaker, yet small\nh and compact. Will fit in\ni a r m W^ere B^ace 8 I\nMODEL 48 COMPLETE\nRadiola 80 (Superheterodyne), $166-00\nra Radiola 82 (Super-Heterodyne) $203-00\nI I\nDELIVERS IT\nTWO STORES\u2014\n18th L Sts. N.W.\u2014North 0790\n18th Col. Rd.\u2014Col. 2900\nColumbia Rd. Store Open Until 10 PM.\nthe lowest number at sets, 23,000.\nNew Mexico, with 28,000 sets, la the\nsecond lowest, while California, with\n1,470,000 receivers, Is the second highest.\nRadio Library Is Mammoth.\nCHICAGO (JP). \u2014The musical library\nof WZNR contains 99,178 sheets of\nmusic, including a complete collection\nof operatic scores. More than 2,000\nphonograph records are also available,\nbesides traps and sound effects of every\ndescription.\nRadio Subscription Is High.\nSubscribers to the radio broadcast\ning service In Germany, which la under\nthe Jurisdiction of the postal depart\nment exceed 3,000,000.\n9","height":"25350","width":"19671"}}
